# Progress Tracking Guidelines

## Progress Documentation
All project progress and changes must be documented in [progress.md](mdc:memory-bank/progress.md)

### Required Updates
1. After completing any feature:
   - Add completion date
   - List implemented functionality
   - Note any technical challenges
   - Document testing results

2. When starting new features:
   - Add planned start date
   - List required components
   - Note dependencies
   - Document acceptance criteria

3. For bug fixes:
   - Document the issue
   - Describe the solution
   - Note any related changes
   - Update affected components

### Progress.md Structure
- Use clear section headers
- Include dates for all entries
- Group related changes
- Link to relevant documentation
- Reference issue numbers if applicable

### Milestone Tracking
- Mark completed milestones
- Update status of in-progress items
- Document any blocked items
- Note dependencies between features

## Change Management
1. Document all significant changes:
   - Technical decisions
   - Architecture modifications
   - Database schema updates
   - API changes

2. Update related documentation:
   - [@architecture.md](mdc:memory-bank/@architecture.md)
   - [@app-design-document.md](mdc:memory-bank/@app-design-document.md)
   - [Tech-stack.md](mdc:memory-bank/Tech-stack.md)

For detailed configuration, see [Tech-stack.md](mdc:memory-bank/Tech-stack.md)
